! Managed by the desktop role (tasks/idle.yml). Appearance of xscreensaver's unlock dialog.
!
! These are X resources, not xscreensaver preferences, and ~/.xscreensaver carries only the
! latter. xscreensaver-auth is an Xt program, so it merges RESOURCE_MANAGER (what `xrdb`
! loads) over its compiled-in app-defaults. The bspwm session script already runs
! `xrdb -merge ~/.Xresources`, which is why they live here. `dialogTheme` is the one
! exception: it is a preference, and idle.yml writes it to ~/.xscreensaver.
!
! Do not put the whole app-defaults file through xrdb; it says so itself. Individual
! resources are fine.
!
! Colours and fonts come from the theme. What is removed here is everything that is not the
! prompt: the hostname, the clock, the "New Login" button (it disappears when its command
! does not exist) and the progress thermometer. The logo and the version heading stay: the
! logo is compiled in and xscreensaver aborts without it, and the heading is a notice the
! author explicitly asks not to be removed.
*passwd.uname:	False
*dateFormat:
*newLoginCommand:
*{{ desktop_xscreensaver_dialog_theme }}.Dialog.thermometer.width:	0
